dalist|[[Martine Dugrenier]]|CAN}}\n|{{flagmedalist|[[Maria M\u00fcller (wrestler)|Maria M\u00fcller]]|GER}}\n|-\n|{{flagmedalist|[[Eri Sakamoto]]|JPN}}\n|-\n|rowspan=2|72 kg<br>{{DetailsLink|2006 World Wrestling Championships \u2013 Women's freestyle 72 kg}}\n|rowspan=2|{{flagmedalist|[[Stanka Zlateva]]|BUL}}\n|rowspan=2|{{flagmedalist|[[Kyoko Hamaguchi]]|JPN}}\n|{{flagmedalist|[[Elena Perepelkina]]|RUS}}\n|-\n|{{flagmedalist|[[Kristie Marano]]|USA}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20060512193547/http://www.fila-wrestling.com:80/download/monsenguan06.pdf Schedule]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20080629222649/http://www.themat.com/specialevents/2006/worlds/default.php Themat.com]\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20061108112016/http://guangzhou.fila-wrestling.com/index.php Official website]\n{{WC FILA}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:2006 Fila Wrestling World Championships}}\n[[Category:2006 in sport wrestling|FILA Wrestling World Championships]]\n[[Category:2006 in Chinese sport|Wrestling World Championships]]\n[[Category:World Wrestling Championships]]\n[[Category:International wrestling competitions hosted by China|Wrestling World Championships]]\n[[Category:2006 World Wrestling Championships| ]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox FILA wrestling event\n|Name = 2006 World Championships\n|Logo = filawrestlinglogo06.jpg\n|Size = 300\n|Host city ={{flagicon|CHN}} [[Guangzhou]], [[China]]\n|dates =25 September \u2013 1 October\n|Stadium = [[Tianhe Gymnasium]]\n|Freestyle = {{RUS}}\n|Greco-Roman = {{TUR}}\n|Women = {{JPN}}\n|Previous = [[2005 World Wrestling Championships|2005]]\n|Next = [[2007 World Wrestling Championships|2007]]\n}}\n\nThe '''2006 [[World Wrestling Championships]]''' were held at the [[Tianhe Gymnasium]] in [[Guangzhou]], [[China]]. The event took place from September 25 to October 1, 2006.\n\n==Medal table==\n{{Medals table\n | caption        = \n | host           = \n | flag_template  = flagcountry\n | event          = \n | team 